text: 4-Phenylazepane, also known as phenazepane, is a chemical compound. It is the base structure in a series of opioid analgesics, including: * Ethoheptazine * Metheptazine * Metethoheptazine * Proheptazine Meptazinol, another opioid analgesic, is a 3-phenylazepane derivative. == See also == * 4-Phenylpiperidine * Azepane Category:Azepanes
title: 4-Phenylazepane
